[2025-12-27 16:55:20] ðŸ’¡ TASK: ### Small, Safe UI Improvement: Add a Loading Indicator to the Navigation Bar

To improve the user experience, we can add a loading indicator to the navigation bar. This will provide visual feedback to the user when they click on a link, indicating that the page is loading.

**Updated Code:**

Add the following HTML and CSS to the `topnav` div in both `index.html` and `games.html`:

```html
<div class="topnav">
  <a href="index.html">Home</a>
  <a href="games.html">Games</a>
  <a href="https://nijikasoftworks.meowcat.site/">News</a>
  <a href="opensource.html">Source Code</a>
  <a href="credits.html">Credits</a>
  <a href="changelog.html">Changelog</a>
  <a href="archive.html">Archive</a>
  <a href="https://neurontechnologies.flarum.cloud/d/3-space-cat-games-general">Help</a>
  <div class="loading-indicator" id="nav-loading-indicator">
    <div class="spinner"></div>
  </div>
</div>
```

```css
.loading-indicator {
  display: none;
  position: absolute;
  right: 20px;
  top: 50%;
  transform: translateY(-50%);
}

.spinner {
  border: 4px solid #eee;
  border-top: 4px solid #e74c3c;
  border-radius: 50%;
  width: 20px;
  height: 20px;
  animation: spin 1s linear infinite;
}

@keyframes spin {
  0% {
    transform: rotate(0deg);
  }

  100% {
    transform: rotate(360deg);
  }
}
```

**JavaScript Code:**

Add the following JavaScript code to both `index.html` and `games.html` to toggle the loading indicator:

```javascript
const navLoadingIndicator = document.getElementById('nav-loading-indicator');

document.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
  if (event.target.tagName === 'A') {
    navLoadingIndicator.style.display = 'block';
    setTimeout(() => {
      navLoadingIndicator.style.display = 'none';
    }, 1000);
  }
});
```

This code will display the loading indicator for 1 second when a link is clicked, providing visual feedback to the user. The indicator will be hidden after 1 second, or when the page has finished loading.
